reviews.headline: Beautiful Color! Easy to use!
reviews.comments: During the holidays, I purchased an eyeshadow stick from MAC. I was thrilled to see that they continued making eyeshadow sticks and purchased the MAC Dazzleshadow Eye Shadow Stick in blue. It's a gorgeous color and so easy to use. I highly recommend it!

reviews.headline: Omg Luv Luv Luv
reviews.comments: So I originally bought this product because I'm not super good at make up and thought it would be like fun to try or whatever. And thank God I bought it because this is the best eyeshadow stick I've ever used. I went out last night for my friends 21st birthday and it was my first time using these sticks and not only did they go on so well the pigment and the glitter lasted all night. I even slept in my makeup woke up this morning, and it was still on my face Not even that I tried to wipe it off with a rag that had warm water on it and it took a decent amount of wipes and there is still glitter on my face like it could not be a more perfect product.

reviews.headline: Glides on, stays put all day
reviews.comments: I tried a couple of shades and I'm particularly obsessed with the "dirty martini" light green shade. It's shimmery and brightens my brown eyes. I glide it over the lash line area, inner corner and outer lid, then blend it in before adding eye liner. It gives a youthful glow to the eyes. Also got the blue metallic shade. It's good but deep. Requires a lot of blending so you don't look like you drew on your eyes with a glittery crayon.  ;)

reviews.headline: Dazzling!!!
reviews.comments: I was so excited to try this eyeshadow pencil in the shade Filthy Martini! It's a beautiful metallic sage green with silver pearls - simply stunning! I found it to be relatively user friendly and the application was seamless. The formula is smooth and creamy with just the right amount of sparkle! I love wearing this product as an eyeliner as well - it really makes my brown eyes pop! The product is buildable and last me an entire day with the use of a setting spray. I love that this can be used as both a day and nighttime look. 10/10 recommend trying! I received this product for free from Topbox Marketing for testing and review purposes.

faceoff_positive.comments:
Instant Glam in a Stick: MAC Dazzleshadow Eye Shadow Sticks - Obsessed!

The MAC Dazzleshadow Eye Shadow Sticks have officially stolen my heart (and my eyelids!). If you're looking for effortless application, intense metallic color, and serious staying power, then look no further. These sticks are a game-changer for adding a touch of dazzling glam to any look in seconds.

The claim of one-swipe color payoff is no exaggeration. The pigmentation is incredible - rich, bold, and truly metallic. Whether you're going for a subtle shimmer or a full-on dazzling eye, these deliver the intensity you need with minimal effort. I love how easily they blend out with just a finger or a brush, allowing for a seamless and professional-looking finish The versatility of these sticks is another major plus. They work beautifully as an all-over shadow for a quick wash of shimmer, but they also perform flawlessly as an eyeliner to add a pop of metallic definition. The dome-tipped stick makes both applications surprisingly precise and easy, even for someone like me who sometimes struggles with eyeliner.

And let's talk about the wear time a solid 12 hours! I've put these to the test through long days and even a bit of unexpected humidity, and they haven't creased or smudged. The fact that they're also waterproof and transfer-resistant gives me so much confidence that my eye look will stay put no matter what.

The range of trendsetting metallic shades is also fantastic. There's a color for every mood and occasion, and I'm already eyeing a few more to add to my collection. They truly inspire you to play up your sparkle and spark your creativity.
faceoff_positive.headline: Am obsession

faceoff_negative.comments:
I love MAC products and own many. I expected this to be more pigmented and less sparkly, so if you're looking for any every day wear shadow this isn't it. This would be a fun going out, extra sparkle to your evening! 

The color itself, I was expecting gold, and it gave more white, which I was shocked about. On the eye, it looked a bit more opaque/transparent as plopped to color on the eyelid. 

The stick, it was a great application and smooth, but it transfers even with eyeshadow primer. So by the end of the night, I had glitter on my cheeks. And even with micellar water, it was tough to get the shimmer off. It doesn't actually come off in its entirety for a few days.

I want to give the benefit of the doubt to other colors but, this was not the best product for me. I think this would be best for certain occasions.

I received this product for free from Topbox Marketing for testing and review purposes.
faceoff_negative.headline: Not What I Expected
